dct_title_s: The Rand-McNally new library atlas map of German Empire (eastern sheet)
dct_description_sm: Running title in margin: Library atlas of the world. [German Empire.]. 63-64. Map of Germany from Berlin and Dresden eastward to present-day Poland. Relief shown by hachures. Ancillary maps: Rhenish-Westphalian industry and mining district -- Berlin, Potsdam and environs. Inset map of northern portion of East Prussia. From: The library atlas of the world. Chicago, New York : Rand McNally & Co., c1912.
